<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-131] Hadoop Consumer goes into an infinite loop when  kafka.request.limit is set to -1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-131</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a bug in  KafkaETLContext.java  where in a new Iterator instance is being created every time. This causes endless loops.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12521223">KAFKA-131</key>
            <summary>Hadoop Consumer goes into an infinite loop when  kafka.request.limit is set to -1</summary>
